<title>Solution</title>
<table id="fs-id1167836580223" class="unnumbered unstyled can-break" summary="This figure says, “Step 1. Read the problem. A figure may help us visualize the situation, then we will create a table to organize the information. Sasheena must mix some of the 25% solution and some of the 50% solution together to get 200 m l of the 40% solution. There are three trapezoids. The first is labeled x and 25%. The second is labeled y and 50%. There are arrows pointing from these two trapezoids to a third which is labeled 40% and 200 m l. The figure says, “Step 2. Identify what we are looking for. We are looking for how much of each solution she needs. Step 3. Name. what we are looking for. Let x = number of m l of 25% solution. Let y = number of m l of 50% solution. A table will help us organize the data. She will mix x m l of 25% with y m l of 50% to get 200 m l of 40% solution. We write the percents as decimals in the chart. We multiply the number of units times the concentration to get the total amount of sulfuric acid in each solution.” The table has four columns and four rows. The columns are labeled, “Type,” and “Number of units times Concentration % = Amount.” Under “Type” are 25%, 50%, and 40%. Under “Number of units” are x, y, and 200. Under “Concentration %” are 0.25, 0.50, 0.40. Under “Amount” are 0.25x, 0.50y, 0.40 times 200. The figure says, “Step 4. Translate into a system of equations. We get the equations from the Number column and the Amount column. Now we have a system.” The equations are x + y = 200 and 0.25x +0.50y = 0.40 times 200. The figure says, “Step 5. Solve the system of equations. We will solve the system of Elimination. Multiply the first equation by -0.5 to eliminate. Simplify and add to solve of x.” The equations then become -0.5 times (x + y) = -0.5 times 200 and 0.25x + 0.50y = 80 or -0.5x -0.5y = -100 and 0.25x + 0.5y = 80 which yield -0.25x = -20 or x = 80. The figure says, “To solve for y, substitute x = 80 into the first equation.” Thus x + y = 200 becomes 80 + y = 200 or y = 120. The figure says, “Step 6. Check. the answer in the problem. 80 + 120 = 200 and 0.25 times 80 + 0.50 times 120 = 200 Yes! Step 7. Answer the question. Sasheena should mix 80 m l of the 25% solution with 120 m l of the 50% solution to get the 200 m l of the 40% solution.">
