<note id="fs-id1168345408192" class="try">
<exercise id="fs-id1168345228558">
<problem id="fs-id1168345559549">
<para id="fs-id1168345197702">Translate to a system of equations and solve:</para>
<para id="fs-id1168345374856">Anatole needs to make 250 milliliters of a 25% solution of hydrochloric acid for a lab experiment. The lab only has a 10% solution and a 40% solution in the storeroom. How much of the 10% and how much of the 40% solutions should he mix to make the 25% solution?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1168341974168">
